text: Betty Kizza (born 23 October 1996) is an Ugandan netball player who represents Uganda internationally and plays in the center position. She has represented Uganda at the 2018 Commonwealth Games and at the 2019 Netball World Cup. In September 2019, she was included in the Ugandan squad for the 2019 African Netball Championships. == References == Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Ugandan netball players Category:Netball players at the 2018 Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games competitors for Uganda Category:2019 Netball World Cup players
